    def GetCustomerDefaultValue(defaultName: str, customerDefaultSearchOption: Session.CustomerDefaultSearchOption) -> Tuple[bool, str]:
        """
         retrieves a customer default value from the database. 
                 There are several different conditions that can arise from 
                querying the database.  First case is the is the record was found and its
                units match. We will return true in this case.  The second case is the record
                was not found. If units given was NXOpen.Session.CustomerDefaultSearchOption.English
                or  NXOpen.Session.CustomerDefaultSearchOption.Metric
                an empty string is passed back, and will return false. 
                
                If the units given was NXOpen.Session.CustomerDefaultSearchOption.None a second andor third attempt is made
                with units NXOpen.Session.CustomerDefaultSearchOption.English then
                NXOpen.Session.CustomerDefaultSearchOption.Metric used instead. The results of
                these attempts can be any of the conditions outlined above.
         
                If you specify either NXOpen.Session.CustomerDefaultSearchOption.English
                or NXOpen.Session.CustomerDefaultSearchOption.Metric for units, this method
                automatically appends _MU or _EU to the input name. For example, if you  specify 
                NXOpen.Session.CustomerDefaultSearchOption.Metric and input the name 
                "UG_gridSpacingY", the function searches for "UG_gridSpacingY_MU".
         
                If you specify NXOpen.Session.CustomerDefaultSearchOption.None for units,
                the function searches for the name as specified. If the name is not found it searches again with _EU
                appended to the name. If the name is still not found, then it appends _MU to the name for its final search.
                
            
         Returns A tuple consisting of (foundCustomerDefault, defaultValue). 
         - foundCustomerDefault is: bool. If customer default was found, returns true .
         - defaultValue is: str. String containing default value. This string will be an empty string if customer was not found. .

        """
        pass
